-- Indonesia Stock Movers: Energi Mega, Indofood Sukses, Unilever
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-01-24T09:22:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/indonesia-stock-movers-borneo-lumbung-energi-indofood-sukses.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 0.2 percent to 3,994.58.
The market was closed yesterday for a public holiday.  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  ,  Indonesia ’s second-
largest listed oil company, advanced 2.5 percent to 205 rupiah
after denying a Kontan report that it may refinance its $200
million debt at Credit Suisse Group.  PT Indofood Sukses Makmur (INDF)  , the parent of the
nation’s biggest instant-noodle maker, climbed 1.6 percent to
4,850 rupiah. Indofood plans to sell 2 trillion rupiah ($223
million) of bonds to refinance debt, Investor Daily Indonesia
reported, citing Werianty Setiawan, corporate secretary at the
company. Setiawan couldn’t comment on the report when called on
her mobile phone.  PT Unilever Indonesia (UNVR)  , Indonesia’s biggest
detergent maker, advanced 4.2 percent to 21,300 rupiah, the
highest close since at least August 1991. The shares gained on
expectation Unilever will report “good” earnings for 2011,
Gifar Indra Sakti, an analyst at PT Sucorinvest Central Gani,
said by telephone. Unilever Corporate Secretary Sancoyo
Antarikso couldn’t be reached when called at his office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
